      "content": "i know i should get a lawyer eventually but i need to know if my foundation is actually solid first. the docs show the Kalsan Regency was a sovereign entity under the 1922 treaty protocols before it was absorbed. if those treaties are still technically valid under modern UN frameworks, does that mean my claim has actual legal weight or is it just a dead end? i need to know if there's a path forward before i spend a fortune on legal fees.",
